====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To make a reply or response to.
#: ''He '''answered''' the question.''
# To respond to a call by someone at a door or telephone, or other similar piece of equipment.
#: ''She '''answered''' the door.''<!-- This meaning is not the same as nº1. Many learners of English have problems understanding how one can answer a door, as a door does not talk -->
# To suit a need or purpose satisfactorily.
#: ''It '''answers''' the need.''
#* '''1903''': [[w:Samuel Butler (novelist)|Samuel Butler]], ''[[w:The Way of All Flesh|The Way of All Flesh]]'', Ch. 41
#*: Theobald spoke as if watches had half-a-dozen purposes besides time-keeping, but he could hardly open his mouth without using one or other of his tags, and "'''answering''' every purpose" was one of them.
# {{legal}} To file a document in response to a [[complaint]].
# To [[correspond]] to; to be in [[harmony]] with; to be in [[agreement]] with.
#*'''1775''': [[w:Richard Brinsley Sheridan|Richard Brinsley Sheridan]], ''[[w:The Duenna|The Duenna]]'', Act 2, Scene 2
#*:''I wish she had '''answered''' her picture as well.''

